Business Brief -- BancTexas Group Inc.:
   Regulators Decide Against
   Pursuing Potential Claims
Separately, BancTexas Group reported a net loss for the
fourth quarter of $344,000, or two cents a share, in contrast
to net income of $33.4 million, or $1.98 a share, in the same
period a year earlier. For the year, the holding company
reported a net loss of $2.9 million, or 17 cents a share,
compared with net income of $27.6 million, or $1.64 a share,
in 1990.
   The year-earlier results included an extraordinary gain of
$36.1 million, reflecting the removal of the flagship bank's
negative net worth from the holding company's balance sheet.